!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

sensitive /ˈsɛnsɪtɪv/

1. ADJ If you are sensitive to other people's needs, problems, or feelings, you show understanding and awareness of them. 有感知力的; 能理解的 [表赞许] 

例： The classroom teacher must be sensitive to a child's needs. 课堂教师必须理解孩子的需求。 

2. sensitively ADV 有感知力地; 能理解地 

例： The abuse of women needs to be treated seriously and sensitively. 虐待妇女的问题需要严肃、小心地对待。 

3. ADJ If you are sensitive about something, you are easily worried and offended when people talk about it. 敏感的 

例： Young people are very sensitive about their appearance. 年轻人对自己的外貌很敏感。 

4. sensitivity N-VAR 敏感 

例： ...people who suffer extreme sensitivity about what others think. …对别人的看法极为敏感的人。 

5. ADJ A sensitive subject or issue needs to be dealt with carefully because it is likely to cause disagreement or make people angry or upset. 敏感的; 棘手的 

例： Employment is a very sensitive issue. 就业是一个非常敏感的问题。 

6. sensitivity N-UNCOUNT 敏感性 [oft N 'of' n] 

例： Due to the obvious sensitivity of the issue he would not divulge any details. 由于问题带有明显的敏感性，他不肯透露任何细节。 

7. ADJ Sensitive documents or reports contain information that needs to be kept secret and dealt with carefully. 机密的 

例： He instructed staff to shred sensitive documents. 他指示员工用碎纸机粉碎机密文件。 

8. ADJ Something that is sensitive to a physical force, substance, or treatment is easily affected by it and often harmed by it. 敏感的 

例： ...a chemical which is sensitive to light. …一种对光敏感的化学品。 

9. sensitivity N-UNCOUNT 敏感性 

例： ...the sensitivity of cells damaged by chemotherapy. …被化疗损害了的细胞敏感性。 

10. ADJ A sensitive piece of scientific equipment is capable of measuring or recording very small changes. 灵敏的 

例： ...an extremely sensitive microscope. …一台极为灵敏的显微镜。 

11. sensitivity N-UNCOUNT 灵敏度 

例： ...the sensitivity of the detector. …该探测器的灵敏度。

</div>

